<item>
            <title>[LU-15476] Our ci processes fail to build master on bionic</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15476</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have a ci process for building various branches on bionic and focal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I recently pulled master from upstream and our bionic builds started failing with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
In file included from include/linux/list.h:9:0,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from include/linux/wait.h:7,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from include/linux/wait_bit.h:8,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from include/linux/fs.h:6,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from /build/lustre-release/lustre/osd-ldiskfs/osd_io.c:45:
/build/lustre-release/lustre/osd-ldiskfs/osd_io.c: In function &#8216;osd_declare_write_commit&#8217;:
/build/lustre-release/lustre/osd-ldiskfs/osd_io.c:1487:34: error: &#8216;LDISKFS_MAX_EXTENT_DEPTH&#8217; undeclared (first use in &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; function); did you mean &#8216;LDISKFS_MAX_TRANS_DATA&#8217;?
&#160; &#160;depth = min(max(depth, 1) + 1, LDISKFS_MAX_EXTENT_DEPTH);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I could disable server but this is a regression I believe ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Upstream bionic cloud image in our ci.</environment>
